Hind-limbs relatively short and robust, heels not meeting when thighs are positioned at right angles to the body, tibiotarsal articulation reaching to commissure of jaw when leg stretched forward; tibia length longer than thigh length; relative toe lengths I <II <V <III <IV; tips of toes round, slightly dilated; toes about one third to two thirds webbed and lateral fringe wide, the webbing formula is I (1) - (2+) II (2-) - (3-) III (
21/2
) - (4-) IV (4++) - (2-) V; inner metatarsal tubercle oval-shaped; outer metatarsal tubercle absent.

