Brachytarsophrys qiannanensis

sp. nov. differs from 

B. platyparietus

by having a smaller size SVL 70.1 mm in male and 80.1 - 84.9 mm in three females (vs. 88.5 - 113.0 mm in males, n = 6 and 118.5 - 131.0 mm in female, n = 3); lateral fringes on toes narrow (vs. wide); brown nuptial pad without nuptial spines present on the dorsal surface of the first finger (vs. dark brown nuptial pads with black nuptial spines present on the dorsal bases of the first two fingers); webbing formula I (1) - (2+) II (2-) - (3-) III (
